tent":"Place garlic, spring onions, parsley and coriander in mixing bowl then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add mushrooms and wine then mix <b>10 sec\/\/speed 1<b>. Pour mushroom mixture over cauliflower in Varoma."},{"content":"Place water in mixing bowl, insert simmering basket, then weigh in sweet potatoes."},{"content":"Place Varoma into position, then steam <b>15-18 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>, or until sweet potato is cooked. Remove Varoma, then remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and set vegetables aside to cool and drain for 5 minutes."},{"content":"Place a large serving bowl on mixing bowl lid, then weigh in currants and baby spinach."},{"content":"Add dried apricots, reserved spice-nut mixture, cooled cauliflower-mushroom mixture and cooled sweet potatoes to serving bowl. Season to taste, then stir through remaining parsley and coriander leaves with spatula."},{"content":"Serve immediately topped with reserved Parmesan cheese or cover and place in fridge until ready to serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Serve cauliflower rice pilaf as a main course by itself or as a side dish. It makes a great salad to take to your next barbecue or picnic."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","4 portions"]}